The best way teams have found this season for calculating Standard Deviations for SetVisionMeasurementStdDevs for field localization involves using Limelights and a CTRE-generated swerve drive. The solution draws from sample code adapted from CTRE Cross The Road Electronics and Limelight’s Megatag2 documentation. Calibration efforts aim to optimize auto alignment for Reef and Human Player Stations. Below is the Java code used in robotPeriodic():  

if (kUseLimelight) {  
    var driveState = m_robotContainer.drivetrain.getState();  
    double headingDeg = driveState.Pose.getRotation().getDegrees();  
    double omegaRps = Units.radiansToRotations(driveState.Speeds.omegaRadiansPerSecond);  

    LimelightHelpers.SetRobotOrientation("limelight-bottom", headingDeg, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);  
    var llMeasurement = LimelightHelpers.getBotPoseEstimate_wpiBlue_MegaTag2("limelight-bottom");  
    if (llMeasurement != null && llMeasurement.tagCount > Constants.LOCALIZATION_MIN_APRIL_TAGS_VISABLE && Math.abs(omegaRps) < Constants.LOCALIZATION_MAX_RPS) {  
        m_robotContainer.drivetrain.setVisionMeasurementStdDevs(VecBuilder.fill(Constants.LOCALIZATION_STD_DEV_X,Constants.LOCALIZATION_STD_DEV_Y,Constants.LOCALIZATION_STD_DEV_THETA));  
        m_robotContainer.drivetrain.addVisionMeasurement(llMeasurement.pose, llMeasurement.timestampSeconds);  
    }
